      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "It's crucial to stay calm and not make adjustments to your insulin dosage without guidance. Since you are experiencing shakiness and sweating, it could indeed be a result of hypoglycemia. However, always monitor your blood glucose levels first. If it's low, consume 15 grams of fast-acting carbohydrates like glucose tablets or juice, then recheck your levels in 15 minutes. If they're still low, take another 15 grams of carbs. If levels are normal, you can resume your regular insulin dose. Stay hydrated and keep a close eye on your glucose throughout your run.",
