      "content": "Dizziness and a spinning head are concerning symptoms, but it's important to remember that insulin can actually worsen hypoglycemia by lowering your blood sugar further. Your immediate response should be to consume another 15 grams of fast-acting carbs to quickly elevate your blood sugar level. Once your blood sugar is back within a safer range, you can then consider adjusting your insulin dose as recommended by your diabetes care team. It's vital to test your blood sugar again after taking additional carbs to ensure it's safe to take any further insulin. Always consult with your healthcare provider before making changes to your insulin regimen. In the meantime, avoid driving or operating heavy machinery until you feel better.",
